This template displays area measurement units used within various [[:Category:Geobox]] templates, automatically converting between metric/imperial values. The input must be unformatted numeric values (i.e. without commas, the commas are automatically added to the output).

It can display and convert following units:
* '''m²''' to '''ft²''' ('''square metres''' to '''square feet''') and vice-versa
* '''ha''' to '''acre''' ('''hectares''' to '''acres''') and vice-versa
* '''km²''' to '''mi²''' ('''square kilometres''' to '''square miles''') and vice-versa

The template has 3 unnamed parameters: <code><nowiki>{{Unit area| unit| value| round}}</nowiki></code>. Their meaning is as follows: 
# '''unit''' … obligatory, unit (<code>sqm/m, sqft/ft, ha, acre, sqkm/km, sqmi/mi</code>, slashes delimit alternatives) of the <code>value</code> aprameter, it will get displayed first
# '''value''' … obligatory, numerical value
# '''round''' … mandatory, number of decimal digits (negative numbers can be used for rounded figures); if not specified 0 is assumed

For examples see [[Template_talk:Unit_area|discussion]].

